    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*karana-%i ‘конец’, ‘край’; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>karan, kanar</w><gloss><q>берег</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>край</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>конец</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>kanār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kerān
                (←*karānya-)</w><gloss><q>сторона</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>направление</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>karana-</w><gloss><q>конец</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>край</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>берег</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Относительно основы см.:
                <bibl><author>Duchesne-Guillemin</author><ref target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX
                866—867</biblScope></bibl>. — Усеченная форма %ikær-%i (см. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_8kær-"/>) выступает в выражении %ikæræj-kæronmæ%i ‘из конца в конец’ и в
            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ægær"/> (из %i*æ-kær%i) ‘чрезмерно’ („без края“).
        Древность усеченной формы находит поддержку в <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
            ><lang/><w>*kara</w></mentioned> в %iha-karam%i ‘однажды’ и %ičiya-kara-%i ‘сколь
        великий’ и в <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
            ><lang/><w>kara-</w><gloss><q>предел</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>круг</q></gloss></mentioned>, рядом с %ikarāna%i (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>X 580, 922</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Konow._Gramm."/><biblScope>108</biblScope></bibl>). — Ос. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_gæræn"/> ‘ограждение’ есть, по-видимому, вариация слова
                %ikæron%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
            52</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica._Suppl."
                /><biblScope>204</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*karana-%i ‘end’, ‘edge’; cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>karan,
            kanar</w><gloss><q>coast</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>edge</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>end</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
                ><lang/><w>kanār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*kerān
                (←*karānya-)</w><gloss><q>side</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>direction</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>karana-</w><gloss><q>end</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>edge</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>coast</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Concerning the stem see:
                <bibl><author>Duchesne-Guillemin</author><ref target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX
                866—867</biblScope></bibl>. — The truncated form %ikær-%i (se <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_8kær-"/>) is used in the expression %ikæræj-kæronmæ%i ‘from end to end’
        and in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ægær"/> (from %i*æ-kær%i) ‘abundantly’ („without any
        borders“). The antiquity of this truncated form is supported by <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                ><lang/><w>*kara</w></mentioned> in %iha-karam%i ‘once upon a time’ and
        %ičiya-kara-%i ‘how great’ and in <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                    ><lang/><w>kara-</w><gloss><q>limit</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w/><gloss><q>circle</q></gloss></mentioned>, close to %ikarāna%i
                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>X 580, 922</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Konow._Gramm."/><biblScope>108</biblScope></bibl>). —
        Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_gæræn"/> ‘barrier’ is apparently a variation of the
        word %ikæron%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
            52</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>.— <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica._Suppl."
                /><biblScope>204</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
